dfischer.utils

Class SymmetricEncryptURLStreamHandlerFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.SymmetricEncryptURLStreamHandlerFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.net.URLStreamHandlerFactory

    public class SymmetricEncryptURLStreamHandlerFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.net.URLStreamHandlerFactory
    A special URL Stream handler factory that implements a new URL protocol named "encrypted" used to load encrypted jar files when executing a load test and decrypt and define the jar files on the fly by using a symmetric key. Note that registering this URL Stream handler factory is needed only once - before decrypting any jar file.
    Since:
    V5.4-K
    See Also:
    ExecAgent.isEncryptJobs(), LoadtestPluginClassLoader, SymmetricEncryptURLStreamHandler, SymmetricEncryptURLConnection, SymmetricEncrypt
